@tayakun (Taya Lindsey) needs no excuse to put together a special look. ⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣
“I love dressing up, whether it’s for going to work, the gas station or an anime convention. I love expressing myself through the way I dress — it could be with makeup, accessories or just the whole outfit. It shows people that I’m going to dress the way I want, whether they like it or not.” ⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣
Taya’s love of cosplay and anime helps them build on outfits they’ve previously worn. “I think about what can make this one better, what can I add to this piece and just do a lot of mixing and matching. ⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣
I get a lot of people telling me they wish they could dress the way I do but are too scared of being judged. Who cares what others think? If you like it, do it.” ⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣
Photo by @tayakun

“Sometimes I think I’m not goated, but then I take a step back and I’m, like, wait — I’m goated.” —Musician EKKSTACY (@ekkstacy)⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
EKKSTACY first started making beats on his grandma’s computer when he was in his mid-teens. “Some not cool things happened to me that led me to start singing and recording music when I was 16. My song ‘I walk this earth all by myself’ changed my life very quickly. I went from working a 9-to-5 in Vancouver to being able to tour and live in LA,” says EKKSTACY, whose sound embraces “elements of indie, punk and shoegaze and a few other things.”⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
“I’m not trying to do anything or force anything, I’m the most impulsive person that I know. I just do what I want in the moment. It works well for me. I’ve always been this way. There’s no plan for me.⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
I like bringing people together. I like seeing everyone having fun and seeing everyone happy. When I do a show and there are 1,000 kids having fun, I did that.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Video of @ekkstacy by @jason_nocito_studio ⁣⁣
Music by @ekkstacy

When you’re @asakemusic, you’re limitless.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The Nigerian-born artist is equal parts music and fashion icon, and during a recent tour stop, his two worlds collided in the most epic way.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Check out our #10Things with the inimitably talented and fashionable Asake ahead of his sold-out stadium show in Brooklyn, New York, last month.⁣⁣

5. The competition was FIERCE.⁣⁣

When @itsyoungmiko (Young Miko) goes into the recording studio, she likes to be comfy.

“I can’t be uncomfortable, otherwise I feel like I won’t be able to flow,” she says, talking about her outfit. “So, comfiness always, but stylish as well.” 😏

Young Miko grew up in Puerto Rico surrounded by music, with family and friends introducing her to rock, reggae and hip-hop in both English and Spanish. “In Puerto Rico, there’s always music playing in every corner,” she says. “Growing up in that environment made it easy for me to approach my music. It was effortless for me.”

Young Miko’s own music is a mix of all her favorite styles, blending genres and languages to create a new take on what Latin music can sound like.

“Latin music has always had an impact, it’s always been a part of the culture,” she adds. “It’s brutal to think that, in the future, my name will be there as well, as part of this movement.”

This Latin Heritage Month, we’re celebrating the global impact of Latin music with some of today’s most exciting, young artists. 🎤💥

Music by @itsyoungmiko

“You’re so much more powerful the more you trust yourself.” —@reneerapp (Reneé Rapp) ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜⁣
⁣
For the 23-year-old musician and actress, trust in herself is what helped launch her onto countless global stages — from Broadway to the big screen — portraying a variety of roles. But her latest endeavor? A tour to celebrate the release of her debut album, “Snow Angel.”⁣
⁣
“Some of my best ideas come from my worst moments. Life just happens, and I’m not asking for it or rejecting it.”⁣
⁣
Check out #10Things with Reneé, her family (and friends-turned-family) ahead of her sold-out show at the Greek Theatre in Los Angeles.⁣
1. Reneé Rapp said get me to the Greek. Literally. ✨🌈❄️⁣
2. Sound check ✅ Vibe check ✅ Handshake check ✅⁣
3. A soon-to-be sold-out theater.⁣
4. “I just kind of throw caution to the wind and see what happens.”⁣
5. Don’t worry, there’s snow cones too.⁣
6. Reneé’s tour family — her incredible band Dre, Nic and Josh x 2 (@drepinckney, @nichumes @josh.porter__, @thejoshfoster).⁣
7. Every 👏 single 👏 time 👏⁣
8. Renee’s family-family — her mom, dad and younger brother on their way to take their seats.⁣
9. This is what a sold-out show (and snow in LA) looks and sounds like.⁣
10. That’s a RAPP on Reneé at the Greek! 🎉❤️‍🔥⁣
